'''Junkyard Lipstick''' were a five-piece, female [[Heavy metal music|metal]] band from [[Cape Town]], South Africa formed in 2011. Their songs are fast-paced, catchy, bass-heavy, and their lyrics incorporate "a playful sense of humour" with an "odd but interesting amalgamation of gore and a more delicate trace of femininity."<ref>Erika Kuenstler, 22 March 2014, Metal Temple magazine, [http://www.metal-temple.com/site/catalogues/entry/reviews/cd_3/j_2/junkyard-lipstick-the.htm Junkyard Lipstick – The Butcher's Delight]. Retrieved 4 September 2014, "......."</ref> In 2016 Junkyard Lipstick disbanded.

==Performance highlights==

The band played at the 2011 and 2012 ''Rock The River'' New Years Festivals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iol.co.za/tonight/music/city-party-central-for-new-year-s-eve-1.1202236?ot=inmsa.ArticlePrintPageLayout.ot |title=News for South Africa and the world |publisher=IOL |date=21 December 2011 |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alteye.co.za/articles/rock-the-river-2011-review |title=ROCK THE RIVER 2011 REVIEW |publisher= Alternative Eye |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref>

In April 2012 Junkyard Lipstick travelled to [[Durban]] to perform at the ''[[Splashy Fen]]'' music festival.<ref>http://www.vaalweekblad.com/139/blogpost/splashy-fen-line-up</ref><ref>http://www.splashyfen.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Splashy-Fen-Artists-1990-2014_TABLE.pdf</ref>

In September 2012, Junkyard Lipstick participated in [[Rolling Stone (magazine)|Rolling Stone South Africa's]] event entitled ''Rolling Stone Weekend''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Stone |first=Rolling |url=http://www.rollingstone.co.za/musicrev/item/1455-rolling-stone-weekend-full-line-up-details |title=Rolling Stone Weekend: Full Line-up Details |work=Rolling Stone |location=South Africa |date=10 September 2012 |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref>

At the end of May 2013, Junkyard Lipstick travelled to [[Gauteng]] where they played the ''Emalyth Arts Expo'' as part of their first ever Gauteng tour.<ref>http://samusicscene.co.za/wp/junkjard-lipstick-gauteng-invasion-win-tickets-and-an-album/</ref><ref>http://www.rockingsa.co.za/events/view/en_us/event_id/105.html</ref>

In March 2014 Junkyard Lipstick played at ''[[RAMFest]]''.<ref>http://metal4africa.com/news/what-does-ramfest-have-in-common-with-metal-and-braaing/</ref><ref>http://mk.dstv.com/2014/02/11/ramfest-2014-cape-town/</ref>

In April 2015, Junkyard Lipstick travelled to [[Gauteng]] to play Africa's largest ever Heavy Metal concert, ''Witchfest''.<ref>http://metal4africa.com/news/two-new-members-for-junkyard-lipstick-in-2015/</ref><ref>http://www.witchfest.co.za/artists/junkyard-lipstick/</ref><ref>http://metal4africa.com/news/witchfest-2015-from-open-air-to-urban-summary/</ref><ref>http://metal4africa.com/news/witchfest-open-air-finalizes-international-line-up-for-2015/</ref>

August 2015 marks the band's debut performance on the Metal4Africa Winterfest line-up.<ref>http://metal4africa.com/m4a_events/m4a-winterfest15-bands-announced/</ref><ref>http://metal4africa.com/interviews/junkyard-lipstick-get-to-know-the-real-jo/</ref>

Junkyard Lipstick was chosen as the main support act for the Cape Town leg of ''Aborted's South African Tour'' August 2015 .<ref>http://metal4africa.com/news/aborted-south-african-tour-local-support-announced/</ref><ref>https://www.witchdoctorproductions.com/aborted-tour-shifted-to-august/</ref> This would be the first time an all-female act supports an international metal band on a South African stage.

